m\": 6385, \"to\": 6441, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kenneth Rooks was in no hurry coming out of the gates in the men's steeplechase final on Wednesday.\", \"from\": 6443, \"to\": 6542, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He knew he just needed to maintain the middle of the pack and take a late charge.\", \"from\": 6543, \"to\": 6624, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And that's exactly what he did.\", \"from\": 6625, \"to\": 6656, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With a little over a lap to go the American looked poised to take the lead and secure a gold medal for Team USA.\", \"from\": 6658, \"to\": 6770, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6693, \"end\": 6701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9559530619193012, \"rank\": 0.026859239876023417, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 6761, \"end\": 6769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9426181884974787, \"rank\": 0.055913485191703007, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 2023 NCAA Division I champ in the 3000-meter steeplechase had calculated it perfectly.\", \"from\": 6771, \"to\": 6861, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite a fall at the last barrier, Rooks was all but guaranteed a medal - it was just a matter of what color.\", \"from\": 6863, \"to\": 6973, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Morocco's Soufiane El Bakkali would end up hawking Rooks down, edging him by .36 seconds for the gold.\", \"from\": 6975, \"to\": 7077, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6975, \"end\": 6982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"score\": 0.9998353678741501, \"rank\": 0.0001645007464043417, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\"}, {\"begin\": 6985, \"end\": 7004, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soufiane_El_Bakkali\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Soufiane El Bakkali\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soufiane_El_Bakkali\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soufiane_El_Bakkali\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rooks beat his personal best time by almost nine seconds to capture America's second silver medalover the last three Olympicsin that event.\", \"from\": 7078, \"to\": 7217, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ryan Canfield contributed to this report.\", \"from\": 7219, \"to\": 7260, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7219, \"end\": 7223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"score\": 0.9909504799420161, \"rank\": 0.009089776168904738, \"text\": \"Ryan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\"}, {\"begin\": 7224, \"end\": 7232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haldimand_County\", \"score\": 0.9999834565236029, \"rank\": 1.6536725643880825e-05, \"text\": \"Canfield\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haldimand_County\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haldimand_County\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Katie Moon was unable to defend herOlympic titlein the women's pole vault in Paris on Wednesday, instead settling for the silver medal after failing to clear 4.90-meters.\", \"from\": 7264, \"to\": 7434, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7270, \"end\": 7274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moon\", \"score\": 0.9999734661712948, \"rank\": 1.7993092599184324e-05, \"text\": \"Moon\", \"types\": [\"Q634\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moon\"}, {\"begin\": 7341, \"end\": 7346, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999878573200333, \"rank\": 1.2142827276742104e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nina Kennedy and Moon were the last two standing in the women's final, and while both failed to clear 4.95m, it was Kennedy's successful attempt at 4.90m that earned her the gold medal.\", \"from\": 7436, \"to\": 7621, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7436, \"end\": 7448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\", \"score\": 0.999999705193816, \"rank\": 2.9480501123672155e-07, \"text\": \"Nina Kennedy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\"}, {\"begin\": 7453, \"end\": 7457, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moon\", \"score\": 0.9999734661712948, \"rank\": 1.7993092599184324e-05, \"text\": \"Moon\", \"types\": [\"Q634\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moon\"}, {\"begin\": 7552, \"end\": 7559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_F._Kennedy\", \"score\": 0.9998400373564692, \"rank\": 0.0001582489634441489, \"text\": \"Kennedy\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_F._Kennedy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_F._Kennedy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Moon, a two time World Champion, earned a medal with a season best of 4.85m.\", \"from\": 7623, \"to\": 7699, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7623, \"end\": 7627, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moon\", \"score\": 0.9999734661712948, \"rank\": 1.7993092599184324e-05, \"text\": \"Moon\", \"types\": [\"Q634\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Canada's Alysha Newman rounded out the top three with her bronze medal finish.\", \"from\": 7700, \"to\": 7778, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7700, \"end\": 7706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.5331569587215217, \"rank\": 0.7786523959552598, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}, {\"begin\": 7709, \"end\": 7722, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alysha_Newman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alysha Newman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alysha_Newman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alysha_Newman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Quincy Hall came from behind to win the men's 400-meter final for his very firstOlympic goldmedal.\", \"from\": 7780, \"to\": 7878, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7780, \"end\": 7786, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\", \"score\": 0.8763883388624192, \"rank\": 0.10361873512454027, \"text\": \"Quincy\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's the United States' first gold in the event since LaShawn Merritt in 2004 - USA swept the medals that year.\", \"from\": 7879, \"to\": 7990, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7888, \"end\": 7901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9507447508803892, \"rank\": 0.044130017200418106, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 7933, \"end\": 7948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LaShawn_Merritt\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LaShawn Merritt\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LaShawn_Merritt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LaShawn_Merritt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It also marks the first medal for the United States since Merritt earned bronze in 2016.\", \"from\": 7992, \"to\": 8080, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8030, \"end\": 8043, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9507447508803892, \"rank\": 0.044130017200418106, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 8050, \"end\": 8057, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LaShawn_Merritt\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1236140525591125e-15, \"text\": \"Merritt\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LaShawn_Merritt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LaShawn_Merritt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hall finished the race in 43.40 seconds, a personal best - he was 0.37 seconds off world-record time.\", \"from\": 8082, \"to\": 8183, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's the fourth individual gold medal for the United States in track and field, joining Noah Lyles (100M), Cole Hocker (1500M), andRyan Crouser(shot put).\", \"from\": 8184, \"to\": 8338, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8230, \"end\": 8243, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.5653141341890966, \"rank\": 0.4290500607676071, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 8272, \"end\": 8282, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 8291, \"end\": 8302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cole_Hocker\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cole Hocker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cole_Hocker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cole_Hocker\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The is an excerpt from a report by Ryan Morik.\", \"from\": 8340, \"to\": 8386, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8375, \"end\": 8379, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"score\": 0.9992814081128635, \"rank\": 0.0006507554657935917, \"text\": \"Ryan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Americans have been there before, but never golden.\", \"from\": 8390, \"to\": 8445, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8390, \"end\": 8403, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"score\": 0.9999999999998863, \"rank\": 1.0850161753466359e-13, \"text\": \"The Americans\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Wednesday, road raceOlympic champion Kristen Faulkner,Chloe Dygert, Jennifer Valente and Lilly Williams defeated New Zealand in the women's team pursuit final to win America's first gold medal in the event, improving on their silver and bronze medals in the past three Olympics.\", \"from\": 8447, \"to\": 8728, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8487, \"end\": 8503, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kristen_Faulkner\", \"score\": 0.9999993389976591, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kristen Faulkner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kristen_Faulkner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kristen_Faulkner\"}, {\"begin\": 8504, \"end\": 8516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chlo\\u00e9_Dygert\", \"score\": 0.9999999166203714, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chloe Dygert\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chlo\\u00e9_Dygert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chlo\\u00e9_Dygert\"}, {\"begin\": 8518, \"end\": 8534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jennifer_Valente\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jennifer Valente\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jennifer_Valente\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jennifer_Valente\"}, {\"begin\": 8539, \"end\": 8544, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Wachowskis\", \"score\": 0.9987044057181192, \"rank\": 0.0009304299439035299, \"text\": \"Lilly\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Wachowskis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Wachowskis\"}, {\"begin\": 8563, \"end\": 8574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_netball_team\", \"score\": 0.9149405631071438, \"rank\": 0.06422472666485128, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_netball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_netball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We knew we had a strong team coming in,\\\" Faulkner said, \\\"and I feel like the lucky one, because they have won medals before on the track and I have not.\", \"from\": 8730, \"to\": 8883, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8772, \"end\": 8780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"score\": 0.999998137287464, \"rank\": 1.221754615703463e-06, \"text\": \"Faulkner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I just wanted to live up to their expectations.\\\"\", \"from\": 8884, \"to\": 8932, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's pretty surreal,\\\" Williams added.\", \"from\": 8934, \"to\": 8972, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do not think anybody expected this.\\\"\", \"from\": 8973, \"to\": 9012, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. clinched the gold medal with an official time of 4:04.306, while the team of Ally Wollaston, Bryony Botha, Emily Shearman and Nicole Shields earned a silver medal with a time of 4:04.927.\", \"from\": 9014, \"to\": 9210, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9100, \"end\": 9114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ally_Wollaston\", \"score\": 0.9999741646459591, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ally Wollaston\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ally_Wollaston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ally_Wollaston\"}, {\"begin\": 9116, \"end\": 9128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryony_Botha\", \"score\": 0.9999999877353504, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bryony Botha\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryony_Botha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryony_Botha\"}, {\"begin\": 9130, \"end\": 9135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Fields\", \"score\": 0.9161149620574854, \"rank\": 0.09125273324867295, \"text\": \"Emily\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Fields\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Fields\"}, {\"begin\": 9149, \"end\": 9163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicole_Shields\", \"score\": 0.9999959818036371, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nicole Shields\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicole_Shields\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicole_Shields\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dygert is on to her second medal of the 2024 Paris Games, claiming bronze in the women's time trial last week.\", \"from\": 9212, \"to\": 9322, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Faulkner is on gold medal No.\", \"from\": 9323, \"to\": 9352, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9323, \"end\": 9331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"score\": 0.9986825882357065, \"rank\": 0.001119492607667134, \"text\": \"Faulkner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"2 after winning the women's road race on Sunday.\", \"from\": 9353, \"to\": 9401, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Associated Press contributed to this report.\", \"from\": 9403, \"to\": 9451, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9407, \"end\": 9423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9999986301096729, \"rank\": 1.3698834338575069e-06, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Australian Olympian Tom Craigbroke his silence on Wednesday after he was\\u00a0arrested in Paris\\u00a0for allegedly buying cocaine after his team fell out of medal contention.\", \"from\": 9455, \"to\": 9619, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9455, \"end\": 9465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9625683542985873, \"rank\": 0.015415313736206963, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 9540, \"end\": 9545, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999980591455332, \"rank\": 1.9408581832082714e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Craig departed a team function on Tuesday night and was arrested about 15 minutes later, the Herald Sun in Australia reported.\", \"from\": 9621, \"to\": 9747, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9621, \"end\": 9626, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Craig_Dean\", \"score\": 0.9988534788317679, \"rank\": 0.0009265670871017684, \"text\": \"Craig\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Craig_Dean\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Craig_Dean\"}, {\"begin\": 9714, \"end\": 9724, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herald_Sun\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.153024292742012e-17, \"text\": \"Herald Sun\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herald_Sun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herald_Sun\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I'd firstly like to apologize for what has occurred in the last 24 hours.\", \"from\": 9749, \"to\": 9823, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I made a terrible mistake.\", \"from\": 9824, \"to\": 9850, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I take full responsibility for my actions,\\\" Craig told reporters as he left the police station,\\u00a0via Reuters.\", \"from\": 9851, \"to\": 9959, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9895, \"end\": 9900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Craig_Dean\", \"score\": 0.9988534788317679, \"rank\": 0.0009265670871017684, \"text\": \"Craig\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Craig_Dean\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Craig_Dean\"}, {\"begin\": 9951, \"end\": 9958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 0.9999999798664023, \"rank\": 1.8290038310877515e-08, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"My actions are my own and in no way, reflect the values of my family, my teammates, my friends, my sport, and theAustralian Olympic team.I have embarrassed you all.\", \"from\": 9961, \"to\": 10126, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am truly sorry.\\\"\", \"from\": 10127, \"to\": 10145, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Australian Olympic Committee\\u00a0spokesperson Dominic Smith said police let Craig off with a warning.\", \"from\": 10147, \"to\": 10244, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10147, \"end\": 10175, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Australian Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 10189, \"end\": 10202, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominic_Smith_(baseball)\", \"score\": 0.7467591400995794, \"rank\": 0.2802768166090242, \"text\": \"Dominic Smith\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominic_Smith_(baseball)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominic_Smith_(baseball)\"}, {\"begin\": 10219, \"end\": 10224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Craig_Dean\", \"score\": 0.9988534788317679, \"rank\": 0.0009265670871017684, \"text\": \"Craig\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Craig_Dean\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Craig_Dean\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris prosecutor's office confirmed that a member of the Australian Olympic team was detained for buying cocaine.\", \"from\": 10246, \"to\": 10363, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10250, \"end\": 10255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999988152234932, \"rank\": 1.1847905452289903e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 10307, \"end\": 10330, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9926774310318912, \"rank\": 0.00737658451696289, \"text\": \"Australian Olympic team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French media, citing police sources, reported Craig allegedly bought about a gram of cocaine.\", \"from\": 10364, \"to\": 10457, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10364, \"end\": 10370, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8656583772650672, \"rank\": 0.1453385465676357, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 10410, \"end\": 10415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Craig_Dean\", \"score\": 0.5608105355945251, \"rank\": 0.7819628373492438, \"text\": \"Craig\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Craig_Dean\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Craig_Dean\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is an except from a report by Ryan Gaydos.\", \"from\": 10459, \"to\": 10506, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10494, \"end\": 10498, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"score\": 0.9993634479811078, \"rank\": 0.0006366222731364225, \"text\": \"Ryan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hampton Morris, the current world record holder in the men's 61-kilogram division, won a bronze medal in the men's weightlifting final on Wednesday to become the firstOlympic medalistin that event for Team USA since 1984.\", \"from\": 10508, \"to\": 10729, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10508, \"end\": 10515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Hampton\", \"score\": 0.9999997616032772, \"rank\": 1.9426947018248778e-07, \"text\": \"Hampton\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Hampton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Hampton\"}, {\"begin\": 10516, \"end\": 10522, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morris_Motors\", \"score\": 0.8052055624336218, \"rank\": 0.10841454983227397, \"text\": \"Morris\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morris_Motors\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morris_Motors\"}, {\"begin\": 10709, \"end\": 10717, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.976565626478261, \"rank\": 0.02388804366474164, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Morris, who set the clean and jerk world record back in April, took home the bronze medal with a score of 298, 12 points behind China's Li Fabin - the reigning gold medalist.\", \"from\": 10731, \"to\": 10905, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10731, \"end\": 10737, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morris_Motors\", \"score\": 0.8052055624336218, \"rank\": 0.10841454983227397, \"text\": \"Morris\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morris_Motors\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morris_Motors\"}, {\"begin\": 10859, \"end\": 10864, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9947296893529477, \"rank\": 0.004098226566701114, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In his Olympic debut, Morris is the youngest lifter to compete for the Americans since Cheryl Haworth competed at the 2000 Summer Games in Sydney.\", \"from\": 10907, \"to\": 11053, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10929, \"end\": 10935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morris_Motors\", \"score\": 0.8052055624336218, \"rank\": 0.10841454983227397, \"text\": \"Morris\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morris_Motors\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morris_Motors\"}, {\"begin\": 10994, \"end\": 11008, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cheryl_Haworth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cheryl Haworth\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cheryl_Haworth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cheryl_Haworth\"}, {\"begin\": 11046, \"end\": 11052, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9992737650871748, \"rank\": 0.0005906450350516029, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"12-times X Games medalist Tom Schaar is taking home a silver medal after he secured his place on the podium in the men's skateboarding park final at the2024 Paris Olympicson Wednesday.\", \"from\": 11057, \"to\": 11241, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11083, \"end\": 11093, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Schaar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Schaar\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Schaar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Schaar\"}, {\"begin\": 11214, \"end\": 11219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999988152234932, \"rank\": 1.1847905452289903e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 24-year-old California native secured a medal position with his second run at La Concorde in Paris, scoring 92.23 points.\", \"from\": 11243, \"to\": 11368, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11259, \"end\": 11269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"score\": 0.6885232533762302, \"rank\": 0.4500830543353266, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\"}, {\"begin\": 11340, \"end\": 11345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999988152234932, \"rank\": 1.1847905452289903e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fellow American Tate Carew found himself in bronze medal position with a run of 91.17, but he was later unseated by Augusto Akio of Brazil.\", \"from\": 11369, \"to\": 11508, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11369, \"end\": 11375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Institute_of_Electrical_and_Electronics_Engineers\", \"score\": 0.8445973987449129, \"rank\": 0.12497079285876236, \"text\": \"Fellow\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Institute_of_Electrical_and_Electronics_Engineers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Institute_of_Electrical_and_Electronics_Engineers\"}, {\"begin\": 11376, \"end\": 11384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9998146349423058, \"rank\": 0.00016865195043685871, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 11385, \"end\": 11389, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tate\", \"score\": 0.9621437178132694, \"rank\": 0.03093987578980224, \"text\": \"Tate\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tate\"}, {\"begin\": 11390, \"end\": 11395, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rod_Carew\", \"score\": 0.9999997729314858, \"rank\": 1.2313308353263907e-07, \"text\": \"Carew\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rod_Carew\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rod_Carew\"}, {\"begin\": 11501, \"end\": 11507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.77812871376329, \"rank\": 0.2079544262254284, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reigning park champion Keegan Palmer of Australia successfully defended his title on the first run, scoring a high of 93.11.\", \"from\": 11510, \"to\": 11634, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11533, \"end\": 11546, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keegan_Palmer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keegan Palmer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keegan_Palmer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keegan_Palmer\"}, {\"begin\": 11550, \"end\": 11559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.849183264612919, \"rank\": 0.17113322367273662, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Steeplechase is an Olympic eventthat was first introduced in 1920.\", \"from\": 11638, \"to\": 11704, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The event's name originated from the horse racing event, where horses would race on a track and navigate various obstacles.\", \"from\": 11705, \"to\": 11828, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It has been standardized to be a 3,000-meter race, or about seven and half laps around a track.\", \"from\": 11830, \"to\": 11925, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The race features 28 barriers, including hurdles and seven water jumps throughout the race.\", \"from\": 11926, \"to\": 12017, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the men's competition the barriers are 36 inches tall and 30 inches tall in the women's competition.\", \"from\": 12019, \"to\": 12122, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The water pit is 12 feet long, and at its deepest point is nearly 20 inches deep.\", \"from\": 12123, \"to\": 12204, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The water pits are sloped from the barrier back inclining toward the track level.\", \"from\": 12205, \"to\": 12286, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The barriers and water jump on the course are fixed, so the athletes can choose if they want to jump over them or use the barriers to propel them into a longer jump.\", \"from\": 12288, \"to\": 12453, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Winfred Yavi of Bahrain won gold in the women's 3,000-meter steeplechase on Tuesday.\", \"from\": 12454, \"to\": 12538, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's steeplechase final is on Wednesday at 3:43 p.m.\", \"from\": 12540, \"to\": 12597, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ET.\", \"from\": 12598, \"to\": 12601, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ryan Canfield contributed to this report.\", \"from\": 12603, \"to\": 12644, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12603, \"end\": 12607, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Aeronautical\", \"score\": 0.9687695141201228, \"rank\": 0.032236986567930594, \"text\": \"Ryan\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Aeronautical\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Aeronautical\"}, {\"begin\": 12608, \"end\": 12616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haldimand_County\", \"score\": 0.9999848319791753, \"rank\": 1.5159193680653038e-05, \"text\": \"Canfield\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haldimand_County\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haldimand_County\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Claire Michel spoke out on social media this week after she was forced to withdraw from the mixed relay event at theParis Olympicsafter she got sick days after competing in the women's triathlon, which included a swim in the Seine River.\", \"from\": 12648, \"to\": 12885, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12648, \"end\": 12661, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claire_Michel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Claire Michel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claire_Michel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claire_Michel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is been a lot of conflicting information in the media lately, so I just wanted to clarify a few things,\\\" she wrote in a post on Instagram.\", \"from\": 12887, \"to\": 13032, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13022, \"end\": 13031, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 0.9999999999947704, \"rank\": 5.201351586894546e-12, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"First of all, thanks to great medical care from both the Team Belgium medical team and the incredible volunteer doctors and nurses at the Polyclinic in the Olympic village, I am gradually doing better and I returned home to Belgium today.\\\"\", \"from\": 13033, \"to\": 13273, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13096, \"end\": 13103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9639619031357529, \"rank\": 0.02317017746448474, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 13258, \"end\": 13265, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9639619031357529, \"rank\": 0.02317017746448474, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Blood tests showed that I contracted a virus (not E. Coli).\", \"from\": 13275, \"to\": 13335, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After three days of vomiting and diarrhea, which left me quite empty, I ended up needing more significant medical attention and spent the Sunday at the clinic.\\\"\", \"from\": 13336, \"to\": 13496, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Michel was one of many athletes to fall ill after the triathlon, leading to speculation that the water in theSeine Riverwas to blame.\", \"from\": 13498, \"to\": 13631, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bacteria levels in the long-polluted river have been in flux during the Games, causing test swims ahead of the triathlon events to be canceled and the men's triathlon to be delayed by a day.\", \"from\": 13633, \"to\": 13823, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers had said that water quality tests done the day of the individual triathlon races showed \\\"very good\\\" levels of fecal bacteria E. coli and enterococci.\", \"from\": 13824, \"to\": 13984, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was initially reported that Michel contracted E. coli, but she clarified Tuesday that she contracted a virus.\", \"from\": 13986, \"to\": 14098, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Several other athletes have since fallen sick with gastrointestinal issues.\", \"from\": 14099, \"to\": 14174, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Associated Press contributed to this report.\", \"from\": 14176, \"to\": 14224, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14180, \"end\": 14196, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9998826275818239, \"rank\": 0.00011705153589210944, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Michelle Obama, the former first lady of the United States, praised American gymnastsSimone Bilesand Jordan Chiles for showing sportsmanship toward Brazil's Rebeca Andrade.\", \"from\": 14226, \"to\": 14398, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14226, \"end\": 14234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\", \"score\": 0.9999931960509915, \"rank\": 6.784067559197854e-06, \"text\": \"Michelle\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\"}, {\"begin\": 14235, \"end\": 14240, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barack_Obama\", \"score\": 0.9999688673948238, \"rank\": 2.7132125069679894e-05, \"text\": \"Obama\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barack_Obama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barack_Obama\"}, {\"begin\": 14271, \"end\": 14284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.6534667952750134, \"rank\": 0.5292821829533603, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 14294, \"end\": 14302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999830153953723, \"rank\": 1.6195259465543977e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 14327, \"end\": 14340, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jordan Chiles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\"}, {\"begin\": 14374, \"end\": 14380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"score\": 0.9156706122338326, \"rank\": 0.08713682635165364, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\"}, {\"begin\": 14383, \"end\": 14397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebeca_Andrade\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rebeca Andrade\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebeca_Andrade\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebeca_Andrade\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles and Chiles took home silver and bronze medals, respectively, on the floor exercise at theParis Olympicswhile Andrade won the gold.\", \"from\": 14400, \"to\": 14536, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14515, \"end\": 14522, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"score\": 0.9999649879035198, \"rank\": 3.382000339687139e-05, \"text\": \"Andrade\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles and Chiles then bowed to Andrade while on 