p://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Of course I will go,\\\" Tentoglou said.\", \"from\": 17990, \"to\": 18028, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"(For 2032), we will see.\", \"from\": 18029, \"to\": 18054, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And also (for 2028), we will see because you never know.\", \"from\": 18055, \"to\": 18111, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But I will try.\\\"\", \"from\": 18112, \"to\": 18128, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tentoglou won gold at the 2024 World Indoor Championships in Glasgow and the 2023 World Championships in Budapest.\", \"from\": 18130, \"to\": 18244, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18191, \"end\": 18198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\", \"score\": 0.9990158127189096, \"rank\": 0.0008958728805995844, \"text\": \"Glasgow\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\"}, {\"begin\": 18235, \"end\": 18243, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"score\": 0.9999997563132025, \"rank\": 2.3995372624411923e-07, \"text\": \"Budapest\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But he has plenty of other gold medals on his docket across the Diamond League, European Championships, European Indoor Championships and junior championships.\", \"from\": 18245, \"to\": 18404, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18309, \"end\": 18323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\", \"score\": 0.8806069012498432, \"rank\": 0.1343241763114566, \"text\": \"Diamond League\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\"}, {\"begin\": 18325, \"end\": 18347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Athletics_Championships\", \"score\": 0.9999953665837233, \"rank\": 3.2098017936992564e-06, \"text\": \"European Championships\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Athletics_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Athletics_Championships\"}, {\"begin\": 18349, \"end\": 18364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Athletics_Indoor_Championships\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"European Indoor\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Athletics_Indoor_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Athletics_Indoor_Championships\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The only silvers he has came in 2022 at the World Championships in Eugene and the 2016 World Junior Championships in Bydgoszcz.\", \"from\": 18406, \"to\": 18533, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18523, \"end\": 18532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bydgoszcz\", \"score\": 0.9999996149056929, \"rank\": 3.8508865471079554e-07, \"text\": \"Bydgoszcz\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bydgoszcz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bydgoszcz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Associated Press contributed to this report.\", \"from\": 18535, \"to\": 18583, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18539, \"end\": 18555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9999987311810037, \"rank\": 7.605590968428108e-07, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Annette Nneka Echikunwoke was set to participate in the women's hammer throw at the2020 Tokyo Olympicsfor Nigeria but a federation error concern drug testing left her unable to compete or even walk in the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 18587, \"to\": 18809, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18675, \"end\": 18680, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.7421433111461773, \"rank\": 0.3472857979142617, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Three years later, Echikunwoke switched countries to the United States and picked up a silver medal at the Paris Olympics on Tuesday.\", \"from\": 18811, \"to\": 18944, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18868, \"end\": 18881, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9845666298971711, \"rank\": 0.010171286977094955, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was the first American woman to earn a medal in the event.\", \"from\": 18945, \"to\": 19007, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18963, \"end\": 18977, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\", \"score\": 0.9999744096770853, \"rank\": 1.3689456954431763e-05, \"text\": \"American woman\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q2188189\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think (this medal) could have happened three years ago, but I am happy it's happening now,\\\" Echikunwoke said.\", \"from\": 19009, \"to\": 19121, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I feel like everything happens for a reason, even if it's bad or good or ugly or whatever the case may be.\", \"from\": 19122, \"to\": 19229, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is beautiful.\\\"\", \"from\": 19230, \"to\": 19249, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Echikunwoke's application to change countries was approved right in time for the 2022 U.S. Nationals and she earned a spot in the World Championships that year.\", \"from\": 19251, \"to\": 19411, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19342, \"end\": 19351, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_Nationals\", \"score\": 0.9495110447640303, \"rank\": 0.04414273375883107, \"text\": \"Nationals\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_Nationals\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_Nationals\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It does not feel real right now,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 19413, \"to\": 19457, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I can not really put it into words.\\\"\", \"from\": 19458, \"to\": 19495, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Associated Press contributed to this report.\", \"from\": 19497, \"to\": 19545, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19501, \"end\": 19517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9999962869429322, \"rank\": 3.6182071387474822e-06, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There will be plenty of opportunities for the United States to add to its medal tally on Wednesday but the spotlight will again be on track and field.\", \"from\": 19549, \"to\": 19699, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19595, \"end\": 19608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.6599387828190955, \"rank\": 0.4720345007980607, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Last night, Cole Hocker and Gabby Thomas picked upgold medalsin their respective events while teammates Yared Nuguse and Brittany Brown received bronze medals.\", \"from\": 19701, \"to\": 19860, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19713, \"end\": 19724, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cole_Hocker